This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the development of a personality model for speech-based conversational agents. It also involves text analysis and natural language processing techniques. Additionally, it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the development of personality dimensions for conversational agents. It could also be categorized under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as it discusses the implications of agent personalities for design and personalization. Furthermore, it could be classified under cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with speech-based conversational agents. Lastly, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves factor analysis and the development of a personality model.
